<br>
The Federation should help to increase the number of Raids and allow to Raid harder Dungeons and Encounters. Another point is to meet new people and it should make pick up groups easier for all.<br>
<br>
<br>
 ** Q&amp;A about Raid **<br>
<br>
Are all Raids Automatically Federation Raids?<br>
No, each Guild can make Guildintern Raids. Our Guild for example do Roleplay specific Raids so we raided Oggok for the Purpose of defeating the world against the evil Ogres. In such Raids there is no place for Large people :-)<br>
<br>
Can i prefer specific Persons for my Raid?<br>
When not all people can go to the Raid Federation poeple should be preferred. <br>
<br>
How can my Guild join this Aliance?<br>
Not decided yet :-))<br>
<br>
<br>
 ** Base Loot Rules **<br>
<br>
These rules are the general guideline assumed to be in effect within the Federation unless additional rules or changes are announced in advance of a raid or a piece of loot dropping. For example Epic pieces go in General to a preanounced Person. <br>
<br>
If you are able to use the item, will use the item, have a need for the item, and feel you have done enough to deserve the item, then you may roll for the item. <br>
<br>
All loot should be rolled for on the basis of the needs of the character in attendance unless agreed upon in advance.  If noone in attendance is able to use a given item, that item will become available for general roll. <br>
<br>
Only the first roll over the correct number range will count.  Those who accidentally roll over incorrect ranges will be allowed to roll again over the correct range. <br>
<br>
Ninja-looting will not be tolerated under any circumstances. <br>
<br>
We would like to encourage members to first attempt to give away or trade items within the Federation before selling or trading them outside the Federation. <br>
<br>
Finally, it is considered to be good form for a portion of all money loot to be donated to the Clerics to help cover the spell component costs incurred to help the group as a whole with buffs. This can be done in many ways and while not required in pick-up groups, it is still encouraged. <br>
